results.name: Expansion of Product_{i>=1, j>=1, k>=1} (1 - x^(i*j*k)).
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000
mathematica: nmax = 52; CoefficientList[Series[Product[(1 - x^(i j k)), {i, 1, nmax}, {j, 1, nmax/i}, {k, 1, nmax/i/j}], {x, 0, nmax}], x]
nmax = 52; CoefficientList[Series[Product[(1 - x^k)^Sum[DivisorSigma[0, d], {d, Divisors[k]}], {k, 1, nmax}], {x, 0, nmax}], x]
a[n_] := a[n] = If[n == 0, 1, -Sum[Sum[d DivisorSigma[1, k/d] DivisorSigma[0, d], {d, Divisors[k]}] a[n - k], {k, 1, n}]/n]; Table[a[n], {n, 0, 52}]
